---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';

const sidebar = [
  {
    label: 'Integrations',
    items: [
      { title: 'Email (SendGrid)', href: '/docs/messaging-integrations#email' },
      { title: 'WhatsApp & SMS (Twilio)', href: '/docs/messaging-integrations#whatsapp-sms' },
      { title: 'FAQ', href: '/docs/messaging-integrations#faq' },
    ],
  },
];
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Messaging Integrations"
  description="Connect your workspace to send and receive WhatsApp, SMS, and Email messages directly in Nero."
  sidebar={sidebar}
  currentPath="/docs/messaging-integrations"
>
  <div class="mb-10" data-animate>
    <span class="section-label mb-4">Guide</span>
    <h1 class="mt-4">Messaging Integrations</h1>
    <p class="text-lg !text-text-secondary">
      Connect your workspace to send and receive WhatsApp, SMS, and Email messages directly in Nero.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== EMAIL ===== -->
  <section id="email" data-animate>
    <h2>Email (SendGrid)</h2>

    <div class="card p-5 mb-6 border-l-3 border-l-primary-300">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-text mb-2">Prerequisites</p>
      <ul class="!mb-0 text-sm">
        <li>A SendGrid account (<a href="https://signup.sendgrid.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sign up free</a>)</li>
        <li>A domain you own (e.g. <code>yourcompany.com</code>)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="step-number text-sm">1</span>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-0">Create a SendGrid API Key</h3>
    </div>
    <ol class="mb-8">
      <li>Go to <strong>SendGrid Dashboard</strong> &rarr; <strong>Settings</strong> &rarr; <strong>API Keys</strong></li>
      <li>Click <strong>Create API Key</strong></li>
      <li>Name it something like <code>Nero Integration</code></li>
      <li>Select <strong>Full Access</strong> (or at minimum: Mail Send + Inbound Parse)</li>
      <li>Click <strong>Create &amp; View</strong> &mdash; copy the key immediately (you won't see it again)</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="step-number text-sm">2</span>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-0">Verify your sender email</h3>
    </div>
    <ol class="mb-8">
      <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> &rarr; <strong>Sender Authentication</strong></li>
      <li>Choose <strong>Single Sender Verification</strong> (quickest) or <strong>Domain Authentication</strong> (recommended for production)</li>
      <li>For Single Sender: enter the email you want to send from (e.g. <code>support@yourcompany.com</code>) and verify via the confirmation email</li>
      <li>For Domain Authentication: follow SendGrid's DNS instructions to add CNAME records</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="step-number text-sm">3</span>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-0">Connect in Nero</h3>
    </div>
    <ol class="mb-8">
      <li>Open Nero &rarr; <strong>Settings</strong> &rarr; <strong>Integrations</strong></li>
      <li>Click <strong>Connect</strong> on the SendGrid card</li>
      <li>Enter:
        <ul>
          <li><strong>API Key</strong> &mdash; paste the key from Step 1</li>
          <li><strong>Sender Email</strong> &mdash; the verified email from Step 2</li>
          <li><strong>Sender Name</strong> &mdash; how your name appears to recipients (e.g. <code>Your Company</code>)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> &mdash; Nero validates your key automatically</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="step-number text-sm">4</span>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-0">Receive incoming emails (optional)</h3>
    </div>
    <p>To receive email replies in Nero, set up SendGrid Inbound Parse:</p>

    <p><strong>Add a DNS MX record</strong> for your domain (or a subdomain like <code>inbound.yourcompany.com</code>):</p>
    <pre><code>Type:     MX
Host:     @ (or inbound)
Value:    mx.sendgrid.net
Priority: 10</code></pre>

    <p>Then in <strong>SendGrid Dashboard</strong> &rarr; <strong>Settings</strong> &rarr; <strong>Inbound Parse</strong>:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Click <strong>Add Host &amp; URL</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Receiving Domain</strong>: your domain (e.g. <code>yourcompany.com</code>)</li>
      <li><strong>Destination URL</strong>: <code>https://nerops.ai/api/webhooks/sendgrid</code></li>
      <li>Leave "POST the raw, full MIME message" <strong>unchecked</strong></li>
      <li>Click <strong>Add</strong></li>
    </ul>

    <p>Incoming emails to your sender address will now appear in Nero conversations.</p>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-surface-alt px-4 py-3 text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2">
      <strong>Pricing</strong> &mdash; SendGrid offers 100 emails/day free. Paid plans start at ~$20/month for 50,000 emails.
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <!-- ===== WHATSAPP & SMS ===== -->
  <section id="whatsapp-sms" data-animate>
    <h2>WhatsApp & SMS (Twilio)</h2>

    <div class="card p-5 mb-6 border-l-3 border-l-primary-300">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-text mb-2">Prerequisites</p>
      <ul class="!mb-0 text-sm">
        <li>A Twilio account (<a href="https://www.twilio.com/try-twilio" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sign up free</a>)</li>
        <li>A phone number (Twilio provides one, or bring your own)</li>
        <li>For WhatsApp: a Meta Business account linked to Twilio</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="step-number text-sm">1</span>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-0">Get your Twilio credentials</h3>
    </div>
    <ol class="mb-8">
      <li>Go to your <strong>Twilio Console</strong> (console.twilio.com)</li>
      <li>On the dashboard, find:
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Account SID</strong> (starts with <code>AC...</code>)</li>
          <li><strong>Auth Token</strong> (click to reveal)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Copy both values</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="step-number text-sm">2</span>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-0">Get a phone number</h3>
    </div>

    <h4>For SMS</h4>
    <ol>
      <li>In Twilio Console &rarr; <strong>Phone Numbers</strong> &rarr; <strong>Buy a Number</strong></li>
      <li>Select a number with SMS capability</li>
      <li>Note down the number (e.g. <code>+31612345678</code>)</li>
    </ol>

    <h4>For WhatsApp</h4>
    <ol class="mb-8">
      <li>Go to <strong>Twilio Console</strong> &rarr; <strong>Messaging</strong> &rarr; <strong>Try it out</strong> &rarr; <strong>Send a WhatsApp message</strong></li>
      <li>For testing, Twilio provides a sandbox number</li>
      <li>For production: connect your own WhatsApp Business number via <strong>Messaging</strong> &rarr; <strong>Senders</strong> &rarr; <strong>WhatsApp Senders</strong></li>
    </ol>

    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="step-number text-sm">3</span>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-0">Connect in Nero</h3>
    </div>
    <ol class="mb-8">
      <li>Open Nero &rarr; <strong>Settings</strong> &rarr; <strong>Integrations</strong></li>
      <li>Click <strong>Connect</strong> on the Twilio card</li>
      <li>Enter:
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Account SID</strong> &mdash; from Step 1</li>
          <li><strong>Auth Token</strong> &mdash; from Step 1</li>
          <li><strong>WhatsApp Number</strong> &mdash; your WhatsApp-enabled number (e.g. <code>+31612345678</code>)</li>
          <li><strong>SMS Number</strong> &mdash; your SMS-enabled number (optional, can be the same)</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> &mdash; Nero validates your credentials automatically</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="step-number text-sm">4</span>
      <h3 class="!mt-0 !mb-0">Set up webhooks for incoming messages</h3>
    </div>
    <p>To receive incoming WhatsApp and SMS messages in Nero:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>In <strong>Twilio Console</strong> &rarr; <strong>Phone Numbers</strong> &rarr; <strong>Manage</strong> &rarr; <strong>Active Numbers</strong></li>
      <li>Click on your phone number</li>
      <li>Scroll to <strong>Messaging Configuration</strong></li>
      <li>Under "A message comes in", set:
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Webhook URL</strong>: <code>https://nerops.ai/api/webhooks/twilio</code></li>
          <li><strong>HTTP Method</strong>: POST</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Click <strong>Save</strong></li>
    </ol>
    <p>For WhatsApp, the webhook is configured through your WhatsApp Sender settings in the same way.</p>

    <div class="rounded-lg bg-surface-alt px-4 py-3 text-sm text-text-secondary mb-2">
      <strong>Pricing</strong> &mdash; Twilio charges per message: ~$0.005/SMS, ~$0.005/WhatsApp (conversation-based pricing). New accounts get trial credit.
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <!-- ===== FAQ ===== -->
  <section id="faq" data-animate>
    <h2>FAQ</h2>

    <div class="space-y-3">
      <details class="card group">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-5 py-4 text-sm font-semibold text-text hover:text-primary transition select-none">
          Are my credentials safe?
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-tertiary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Yes. Your API keys and tokens are encrypted with AES-256 before being stored. They are never visible in the app — only our secure server-side functions can decrypt them to send messages.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="card group">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-5 py-4 text-sm font-semibold text-text hover:text-primary transition select-none">
          Can I connect both SendGrid and Twilio?
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-tertiary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Yes. Each integration works independently. You can have email via SendGrid and WhatsApp/SMS via Twilio at the same time.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="card group">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-5 py-4 text-sm font-semibold text-text hover:text-primary transition select-none">
          Can different workspaces have different integrations?
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-tertiary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Yes. Each workspace has its own separate credentials and configuration. One workspace's integration has no access to another's.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="card group">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-5 py-4 text-sm font-semibold text-text hover:text-primary transition select-none">
          What happens if I disconnect an integration?
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-tertiary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Your existing conversation history stays intact. You just won't be able to send or receive new messages through that channel until you reconnect.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="card group">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer px-5 py-4 text-sm font-semibold text-text hover:text-primary transition select-none">
          I'm not receiving incoming messages — what should I check?
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-text-tertiary group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-5 pb-4 text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          <ul class="mt-1">
            <li>Verify your webhook URL is correct in Twilio/SendGrid settings</li>
            <li>Check that your DNS MX record is set up (for email)</li>
            <li>Make sure the integration is active (green checkmark) in Nero settings</li>
            <li>For Twilio: ensure the phone number has the webhook configured</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-border-subtle">
    <p class="text-sm text-text-tertiary">
      Need help? Reach out at <a href="mailto:support@nerops.ai">support@nerops.ai</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
